parameters.name: model_id
parameters.label: model_id
parameters.help: Destination id for this model; auto-generated if not specified.

parameters.name: training_frame
parameters.label: training_frame
parameters.help: Id of the training data frame.

parameters.name: validation_frame
parameters.label: validation_frame
parameters.help: Id of the validation data frame.

parameters.name: nfolds
parameters.label: nfolds
parameters.help: Number of folds for K-fold cross-validation (0 to disable or >= 2).

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.help: Whether to keep the predictions of the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation fold assignment.

parameters.name: score_each_iteration
parameters.label: score_each_iteration
parameters.help: Whether to score during each iteration of model training.

parameters.name: score_tree_interval
parameters.label: score_tree_interval
parameters.help: Score the model after every so many trees. Disabled if set to 0.

parameters.name: fold_assignment
parameters.label: fold_assignment
parameters.help: Cross-validation fold assignment scheme, if fold_column is not specified. The 'Stratified' option will stratify the folds based on the response variable, for classification problems.

parameters.name: fold_column
parameters.label: fold_column
parameters.help: Column with cross-validation fold index assignment per observation.

parameters.name: response_column
parameters.label: response_column
parameters.help: Response variable column.

parameters.name: ignored_columns
parameters.label: ignored_columns
parameters.help: Names of columns to ignore for training.

parameters.name: ignore_const_cols
parameters.label: ignore_const_cols
parameters.help: Ignore constant columns.

parameters.name: offset_column
parameters.label: offset_column
parameters.help: Offset column. This will be added to the combination of columns before applying the link function.

parameters.name: weights_column
parameters.label: weights_column
parameters.help: Column with observation weights. Giving some observation a weight of zero is equivalent to excluding it from the dataset; giving an observation a relative weight of 2 is equivalent to repeating that row twice. Negative weights are not allowed. Note: Weights are per-row observation weights and do not increase the size of the data frame. This is typically the number of times a row is repeated, but non-integer values are supported as well. During training, rows with higher weights matter more, due to the larger loss function pre-factor. If you set weight = 0 for a row, the returned prediction frame at that row is zero and this is incorrect. To get an accurate prediction, remove all rows with weight == 0.

parameters.name: balance_classes
parameters.label: balance_classes
parameters.help: Balance training data class counts via over/under-sampling (for imbalanced data).

parameters.name: class_sampling_factors
parameters.label: class_sampling_factors
parameters.help: Desired over/under-sampling ratios per class (in lexicographic order). If not specified, sampling factors will be automatically computed to obtain class balance during training. Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_after_balance_size
parameters.label: max_after_balance_size
parameters.help: Maximum relative size of the training data after balancing class counts (can be less than 1.0). Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.label: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.help: [Deprecated] Maximum size (# classes) for confusion matrices to be printed in the Logs

parameters.name: ntrees
parameters.label: ntrees
parameters.help: Number of trees.

parameters.name: max_depth
parameters.label: max_depth
parameters.help: Maximum tree depth (0 for unlimited).

parameters.name: min_rows
parameters.label: min_rows
parameters.help: Fewest allowed (weighted) observations in a leaf.

parameters.name: nbins
parameters.label: nbins
parameters.help: For numerical columns (real/int), build a histogram of (at least) this many bins, then split at the best point

parameters.name: nbins_top_level
parameters.label: nbins_top_level
parameters.help: For numerical columns (real/int), build a histogram of (at most) this many bins at the root level, then decrease by factor of two per level

parameters.name: nbins_cats
parameters.label: nbins_cats
parameters.help: For categorical columns (factors), build a histogram of this many bins, then split at the best point. Higher values can lead to more overfitting.

parameters.name: r2_stopping
parameters.label: r2_stopping
parameters.help: r2_stopping is no longer supported and will be ignored if set - please use stopping_rounds, stopping_metric and stopping_tolerance instead. Previous version of H2O would stop making trees when the R^2 metric equals or exceeds this

parameters.name: stopping_rounds
parameters.label: stopping_rounds
parameters.help: Early stopping based on convergence of stopping_metric. Stop if simple moving average of length k of the stopping_metric does not improve for k:=stopping_rounds scoring events (0 to disable)

parameters.name: stopping_metric
parameters.label: stopping_metric
parameters.help: Metric to use for early stopping (AUTO: logloss for classification, deviance for regression and anomaly_score for Isolation Forest). Note that custom and custom_increasing can only be used in GBM and DRF with the Python client.

parameters.name: stopping_tolerance
parameters.label: stopping_tolerance
parameters.help: Relative tolerance for metric-based stopping criterion (stop if relative improvement is not at least this much)

parameters.name: max_runtime_secs
parameters.label: max_runtime_secs
parameters.help: Maximum allowed runtime in seconds for model training. Use 0 to disable.

parameters.name: seed
parameters.label: seed
parameters.help: Seed for pseudo random number generator (if applicable)

parameters.name: build_tree_one_node
parameters.label: build_tree_one_node
parameters.help: Run on one node only; no network overhead but fewer cpus used. Suitable for small datasets.

parameters.name: learn_rate
parameters.label: learn_rate
parameters.help: Learning rate (from 0.0 to 1.0)

parameters.name: learn_rate_annealing
parameters.label: learn_rate_annealing
parameters.help: Scale the learning rate by this factor after each tree (e.g., 0.99 or 0.999)

parameters.name: distribution
parameters.label: distribution
parameters.help: Distribution function

parameters.name: quantile_alpha
parameters.label: quantile_alpha
parameters.help: Desired quantile for Quantile regression, must be between 0 and 1.

parameters.name: tweedie_power
parameters.label: tweedie_power
parameters.help: Tweedie power for Tweedie regression, must be between 1 and 2.

parameters.name: huber_alpha
parameters.label: huber_alpha
parameters.help: Desired quantile for Huber/M-regression (threshold between quadratic and linear loss, must be between 0 and 1).

parameters.name: checkpoint
parameters.label: checkpoint
parameters.help: Model checkpoint to resume training with.

parameters.name: sample_rate
parameters.label: sample_rate
parameters.help: Row sample rate per tree (from 0.0 to 1.0)

parameters.name: sample_rate_per_class
parameters.label: sample_rate_per_class
parameters.help: A list of row sample rates per class (relative fraction for each class, from 0.0 to 1.0), for each tree

parameters.name: col_sample_rate
parameters.label: col_sample_rate
parameters.help: Column sample rate (from 0.0 to 1.0)

parameters.name: col_sample_rate_change_per_level
parameters.label: col_sample_rate_change_per_level
parameters.help: Relative change of the column sampling rate for every level (must be > 0.0 and <= 2.0)

parameters.name: col_sample_rate_per_tree
parameters.label: col_sample_rate_per_tree
parameters.help: Column sample rate per tree (from 0.0 to 1.0)

parameters.name: min_split_improvement
parameters.label: min_split_improvement
parameters.help: Minimum relative improvement in squared error reduction for a split to happen

parameters.name: histogram_type
parameters.label: histogram_type
parameters.help: What type of histogram to use for finding optimal split points

parameters.name: max_abs_leafnode_pred
parameters.label: max_abs_leafnode_pred
parameters.help: Maximum absolute value of a leaf node prediction

parameters.name: pred_noise_bandwidth
parameters.label: pred_noise_bandwidth
parameters.help: Bandwidth (sigma) of Gaussian multiplicative noise ~N(1,sigma) for tree node predictions

parameters.name: categorical_encoding
parameters.label: categorical_encoding
parameters.help: Encoding scheme for categorical features

parameters.name: calibrate_model
parameters.label: calibrate_model
parameters.help: Use Platt Scaling (default) or Isotonic Regression to calculate calibrated class probabilities. Calibration can provide more accurate estimates of class probabilities.

parameters.name: calibration_frame
parameters.label: calibration_frame
parameters.help: Data for model calibration

parameters.name: calibration_method
parameters.label: calibration_method
parameters.help: Calibration method to use

parameters.name: custom_metric_func
parameters.label: custom_metric_func
parameters.help: Reference to custom evaluation function, format: `language:keyName=funcName`

parameters.name: custom_distribution_func
parameters.label: custom_distribution_func
parameters.help: Reference to custom distribution, format: `language:keyName=funcName`

parameters.name: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.label: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.help: Automatically export generated models to this directory.

parameters.name: in_training_checkpoints_dir
parameters.label: in_training_checkpoints_dir
parameters.help: Create checkpoints into defined directory while training process is still running. In case of cluster shutdown, this checkpoint can be used to restart training.

parameters.name: in_training_checkpoints_tree_interval
parameters.label: in_training_checkpoints_tree_interval
parameters.help: Checkpoint the model after every so many trees. Parameter is used only when in_training_checkpoints_dir is defined

parameters.name: monotone_constraints
parameters.label: monotone_constraints
parameters.help: A mapping representing monotonic constraints. Use +1 to enforce an increasing constraint and -1 to specify a decreasing constraint.

parameters.name: check_constant_response
parameters.label: check_constant_response
parameters.help: Check if response column is constant. If enabled, then an exception is thrown if the response column is a constant value.If disabled, then model will train regardless of the response column being a constant value or not.

parameters.name: gainslift_bins
parameters.label: gainslift_bins
parameters.help: Gains/Lift table number of bins. 0 means disabled.. Default value -1 means automatic binning.

parameters.name: auc_type
parameters.label: auc_type
parameters.help: Set default multinomial AUC type.

parameters.name: interaction_constraints
parameters.label: interaction_constraints
parameters.help: A set of allowed column interactions.

parameters.name: auto_rebalance
parameters.label: auto_rebalance
parameters.help: Allow automatic rebalancing of training and validation datasets
